The paper proposes a method for unsupervised style modeling and control in speech synthesis, which falls under the categories of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Specifically, the paper focuses on end-to-end speech synthesis, which involves generating speech directly from text input. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (sound), which covers research related to speech and audio processing. 

The paper also discusses the use of embeddings and training without explicit labels, which are common techniques in NLP and ML. Therefore, cs.CL (computation and language) is another likely category. 

Additionally, the paper mentions the use of interpretable labels and style transfer, which are related to the fields of data mining and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (learning) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence) are also possible categories.
